Description. Mostly yellow to orange, with white to pale yellow markings. Setae dark red brown to black. Head (
Figs. 13–16
): Yellow to orange except ocellar tubercle brown. 3–4 frontal setae; 2 orbital setae, posterior seta well developed. Ocellar seta weak, at most 1.5 times as long as ocellar tubercle. Facial carina, in profile, strongly produced and convex near midheight. Antenna extended ca. 0.67 distance to ventral facial margin. Female arista (
Fig. 14
) filiform; male arista (
Fig. 13
) with short triangular preapical expansion. Palpus (
Fig. 16
) in lateral view parallel-sided or slightly expanded on apical half, rounded truncate apically, unevenly setulose, with subapical ventral area with denser and some larger setulae, apical bare area, and 2–3 larger marginal apical setulae.

Female terminalia: Oviscape 3.08–3.60 mm long, 0.69–0.77 times as long as mesonotum, straight in lateral view, entirely yellow to orange; spiracle at basal 0.31–0.38 . Eversible membrane (
Fig. 52
) with numerous short stout denticles and 50–70 medium length hooklike dorsobasal denticles in 6–7 V-shaped rows in subtriangular pattern. Aculeus ( Figs. 73, 74 ) straight in lateral view, 1.78–1.98 mm long, 0.54–0.60 times as long as oviscape, in ventral view base strongly expanded, 0.27–0.32 mm wide; shaft 0.085 –0.100 mm wide at midlength; tip (
Fig. 87
) 0.25–0.29 mm long, 0.14–0.15 times aculeus length, 0.090–0.105 mm wide, 2.60–2.89 times as long as wide, very weakly constricted basally or weakly expanded subbasally, lateral margin slightly convex and gradually tapered to blunt apex, nonserrate, 0.07–0.08 mm wide in lateral view, 0.71–0.80 times ventral width. Spermathecae not examined.
